title: Translate to structured data
description: Storage the semi-structured and unstructured part of user-set information.

notes.note: Think of the stucture of these data, including text and so on.

Mysql could storage structured data, but there are lots of semi-structured and unstructured data. There are two ways to store these data. One is translate them to binary data. But this way may cause database performance degradation and can be complex to deal with.So I try to storage them into a folder named media(deal with the video and image users upload) and another folder named static(deal with the static picture and video), then save the data stored in the two folders to database(MySQL)
